Country abbreviations

all_countries.Rd

A string list containing all known countries in abbreviated format. 3-letter codes are analyzed as separate countries. The 3-letter codes conform to ISO naming conventions. 4-letter codes are not ISO codes but still analyzed as separate countries. 5-letter codes (and longer) are aggregations.

Usage

all_countries

Format

A string list with 166 entries.

Examples

all_countries

#> [1] "AFRI"
